column20: IT - from web design and programming to learning about Open source software and promoting it wherever possible. Languages - I've studied Spanish for 7 years, German for 3, Italian for about a year in my own time and I'm always open to learning new languages and the root of languages. I find it really cool to notice the similarities between all the Latin based languages like Spanish, french and Italian. Photography - a hobby now for about 5/6 years, I purchased a basic DSLRall those years ago and haven't looked back. I've studied it, read books in my own time, and had my work displayed in a couple of local galleries. I also enjoy a little bit of digital photo manipulation...but I can control my urges in public. Comedy - I am a huge fan of the art of stand up comedy. In my opinion it is one of the most underrated forms of performance.
